# Standards: Data Schemas & Models

## 1. Objective
To enforce strict structural contracts between Deterministic Code (Ingestion/Rendering) and Probabilistic Agents (LLMs). All JSON outputs must validate against these schemas before being processed by the next stage.

## 2. Core Data Models

### 2.1 Raw Item (`raw_item.schema.json`)
Produced by: **Ingestion Layer**
Consumed by: **ItemSummarizerAgent**

```json
{
  "type": "object",
  "required": ["id", "title", "url", "published_at", "type", "content", "source_id"],
  "properties": {
    "id": { "type": "string", "description": "Unique hash of the URL" },
    "title": { "type": "string" },
    "url": { "type": "string", "format": "uri" },
    "published_at": { "type": "string", "format": "date-time" },
    "type": { "type": "string", "enum": ["article", "video", "blog", "research", "opinion"] },
    "source_id": { "type": "string", "description": "Key from sources.json" },
    "source_type": { "type": "string", "enum": ["research", "news", "vendor", "indie"] },
    "content": { "type": "string", "minLength": 100 },
    "tags": { "type": "array", "items": { "type": "string" } }
  }
}
```

###2.2 Item Summary (item_summary.schema.json)
Produced by: ItemSummarizerAgent Consumed by: NewsletterEditorAgent

```json
{
  "type": "object",
  "required": ["id", "summary", "safety_flag", "safety_comment"],
  "properties": {
    "id": { "type": "string" },
    "summary": { 
      "type": "string", 
      "maxLength": 600, 
      "description": "Concise summary approx 80 words." 
    },
    "topics": { 
      "type": "array", 
      "items": { "type": "string" },
      "description": "Populated by TopicClassifierAgent"
    },
    "safety_flag": { "type": "boolean" },
    "safety_comment": { "type": "string" }
  }
}
```
### 2.3 Newsletter Spec (newsletter_spec.schema.json)
Produced by: NewsletterEditorAgent Consumed by: Renderer, Critics

```json
{
  "type": "object",
  "required": ["week_label", "intro", "sections", "closing_note"],
  "properties": {
    "week_label": { "type": "string" },
    "intro": { "type": "string" },
    "sections": {
      "type": "array",
      "items": {
        "type": "object",
        "required": ["name", "items"],
        "properties": {
          "name": { "type": "string" },
          "items": {
            "type": "array",
            "items": { "$ref": "#/definitions/ItemSummary" }
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "closing_note": { "type": "string" }
  }
}
```
## 3. Governance Models
###3.1 Critic Report (critic_report.schema.json)
Produced by: Critic Agents

```json
{
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "factual": {
      "has_unsupported_claims": { "type": "boolean" },
      "unsupported_claims": { "type": "array", "items": { "type": "string" } }
    },
    "tone_safety": {
      "tone_ok": { "type": "boolean" },
      "safety_ok": { "type": "boolean" },
      "issues": { "type": "array", "items": { "type": "string" } }
    },
    "privacy": {
      "privacy_ok": { "type": "boolean" },
      "flagged_segments": { "type": "array", "items": { "type": "string" } }
    }
  }
}
```
## 4. Operational Models
### 4.1 Run Metrics (run_metrics.schema.json)
Produced by: Pipeline Runner

```json
{
  "type": "object",
  "required": ["status", "items_ingested", "items_published"],
  "properties": {
    "week_label": { "type": "string" },
    "status": { "type": "string", "enum": ["SUCCESS", "FAILED", "PARTIAL"] },
    "timestamp": { "type": "string", "format": "date-time" },
    "items_ingested": { "type": "integer" },
    "items_summarized": { "type": "integer" },
    "items_published": { "type": "integer" },
    "errors": { "type": "array", "items": { "type": "string" } }
  }
}
```

## 5. Validation Rules
Strict Mode: All LLM outputs must be validated against these schemas using a library like jsonschema.

Fail-Fast: If an agent produces invalid JSON that cannot be parsed, the item is marked as FAILED_SCHEMA and excluded. Do not attempt to "guess" the structure.